"He has a lot of faith in himself".
He's in the Hall of Fame and he's given so much to these teams before and also this week.
I didn't think he'd play two games.
I imagined he'd play more, but that's how it happened, and that's how it should be.
He wants to be out there like everybody else".
On Sunday, Mickelson will beat Nick Faldo's record for most Ryder Cup games played.
It could be the end of a Ryder Cup career that has never quite matched his individual performance.
Mickelson has 18 wins, 20 losses and seven draws, although Furyk said his presence contributes something indefinable.
"He's funny, he's sarcastic, he's funny, he likes to pick on people, and he's good to have in the team room", he explained.
